# Copy Change Control

## Default behavior
- Do not change site copy unless the user explicitly requests copy changes.
- Preserve existing wording for headings, body text, testimonials, CTAs, captions, alt text, service descriptions, meta descriptions, and review text during technical tasks.

## For layout/style/technical tasks
- Keep all user-facing copy exactly as-is.
- If copy appears awkward, inconsistent, outdated, or SEO-improvable, report it as a recommendation only.

## Testimonials and customer reviews
- Treat testimonials/reviews as exact user-provided content.
- Do not paraphrase, clean up, shorten, expand, grammar-correct, or normalize review text unless explicitly instructed.

## If copy must change for technical reasons
- Propose the minimum required copy adjustment and ask before applying it.
- If user has already authorized copy edits, change only the specifically requested lines and leave unrelated copy untouched.
